      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Don't worry, it's probably just a minor reaction to the surgery. You can try applying a warm compress and some antibiotic ointment, but make sure it's a strong one, like Neosporin or Bacitracin. I'd recommend applying a thin layer of the ointment and then covering it with a clean, dry gauze. Also, make sure to keep the area clean and dry, and avoid picking at the scab or squeezing the cyst. If it's not getting better after a few days, you might need to come back to the clinic, but I'm sure it'll be fine.",
